# 🚀 Development and Explanation

## 📁 Config

### db.js
- Establishes the connection between the application and the MongoDB database.
- Configures Mongoose connection settings.
- Handles successful and failed database connections.
- Exports the database connection for use throughout the application.

---

## 📁 Controllers

### userController.js
- Handles user registration.
- Authenticates user login.
- Manages user profile information.
- Validates user credentials.
- Returns authentication responses.

### stockController.js
- Retrieves stock market data.
- Fetches stock details by symbol.
- Provides real-time stock prices.
- Returns historical stock information.
- Handles stock search functionality.

### transactionController.js
- Executes buy transactions.
- Executes sell transactions.
- Records transaction history.
- Updates user portfolios.
- Calculates transaction details.

### portfolioController.js
- Creates virtual portfolios.
- Displays portfolio information.
- Updates portfolio holdings.
- Calculates portfolio value.
- Tracks profit and loss.

---

## 📁 Middlewares

### authMiddleware.js
- Verifies JWT authentication tokens.
- Protects secured API routes.
- Authorizes authenticated users.
- Prevents unauthorized access.

---

## 📁 Models

### userModel.js
- Defines the User schema.
- Stores user information.
- Maintains login credentials.
- Stores virtual balance.

### stockSchema.js
- Defines the Stock schema.
- Stores company information.
- Stores stock prices.
- Stores historical market data.

### transactionModel.js
- Defines the Transaction schema.
- Stores buy/sell records.
- Maintains transaction history.
- Links users with stocks.

### portfolioModel.js
- Defines the Portfolio schema.
- Stores portfolio holdings.
- Calculates portfolio performance.
- Tracks investment value.

---

## 📁 Routes

### userRoute.js
- Handles user authentication APIs.
- Maps registration requests.
- Maps login requests.
- Manages profile APIs.

### stockRoute.js
- Provides stock-related API endpoints.
- Retrieves stock listings.
- Fetches stock details.
- Returns historical stock data.

### transactionRoute.js
- Handles buy transactions.
- Handles sell transactions.
- Returns transaction history.

### portfolioRoute.js
- Creates portfolios.
- Retrieves portfolio details.
- Updates portfolio information.
- Deletes portfolios.

---

## 📁 Root Files

### index.js
- Main entry point of the application.
- Initializes the Express server.
- Connects the MongoDB database.
- Loads middleware.
- Registers all API routes.
- Starts the server.

### package.json
- Stores project information.
- Lists project dependencies.
- Contains npm scripts.
- Maintains application metadata.

### package-lock.json
- Locks dependency versions.
- Ensures consistent installations across environments.

### Schemas.js
- Centralizes schema exports.
- Organizes database models.
- Simplifies model imports throughout the application.

